docs.abstract: Democrats and Republicans at both the federal and state levels are uniting to investigate the power of Big Tech and, potentially, to rein in the dominant companies.
docs.snippet: Democrats and Republicans at both the federal and state levels are uniting to investigate the power of Big Tech and, potentially, to rein in the dominant companies.
docs.lead_paragraph: There is a major force uniting America’s fiercely partisan politicians: big technology companies. Democrats and Republicans at the federal and state levels are coming together to scrutinize the power of the Silicon Valley giants and, potentially, to rein them in.

headline.main: New Google and Facebook Inquiries Show Big Tech Scrutiny Is Rare Bipartisan Act
headline.print_headline: New Inquiries Show Big Tech Scrutiny Is Rare Bipartisan Act

docs.abstract: With the German and Italian economies in trouble, a so-called “hard Brexit” could tip the entire continent toward a recession.
docs.snippet: With the German and Italian economies in trouble, a so-called “hard Brexit” could tip the entire continent toward a recession.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — For a major economy, the best time to descend into befuddling uncertainty over the rules that govern trade is never. As the European Union now confronts the prospect that Britain may bolt its ranks without a deal, most likely triggering mayhem, this is an especially unfortunate moment.

headline.main: For Europe, the Threat of a No-Deal Brexit Comes at a Bad Time
headline.print_headline: No-Deal Brexit May Push Continent Into Recession

docs.abstract: Medical groups are warning that new federal data-sharing rules, enabling people to get their health records through a smartphone, could lead to invasions of privacy.
docs.snippet: Medical groups are warning that new federal data-sharing rules, enabling people to get their health records through a smartphone, could lead to invasions of privacy.
docs.lead_paragraph: Americans may soon be able to get their medical records through smartphone apps as easily as they order takeout food from Seamless or catch a ride from Lyft.

headline.main: When Apps Get Your Medical Data, Your Privacy May Go With It
headline.print_headline: Battle Brews Over Moving Health Records to the Cloud

docs.abstract: Facing a labor shortage, restaurants are turning to on-demand services for line cooks, dishwashers and other trained workers.
docs.snippet: Facing a labor shortage, restaurants are turning to on-demand services for line cooks, dishwashers and other trained workers.
docs.lead_paragraph: As he wrapped up a brunch shift at the Australian cafe Two Hands in the Little Italy section of Manhattan, Christopher Mortenson saw his phone light up. All afternoon, he had been waiting for the notification: ABC Cocina, an upscale Latin American restaurant in the Flatiron district, needed a line cook. He had an hour to get there.

headline.main: Cooking Eggs in the Morning and Shucking Oysters at Night, Thanks to an App
headline.print_headline: Cooks Adopt Apps To Snap Up Shifts
